President Trump delivered a speech in Poland, titled "Remarks to the people of Poland," which showcased his nation-state populism. He emphasized the importance of defending Western values and protecting borders. Trump highlighted the significance of non-liberal democratic institutions such as family, faith, military, and police in enforcing liberal democratic values. He called for a reinvigoration of national spirit and pride in America and its allies. The speech described a world of sovereign nation-states united against the enemies of civilization. Trump challenged the audience to question if they still possessed the determination and resilience of previous generations.